page.title: 07Blackdown Wood
page.content: This{wood}belongs to{Dr. Katherine {Wyndham. }It is 20 hectares. I found a piece of wood that was shaped like a sea shell and I found a rotten piece of wood with holes in it. I also found an eaten fir cone. We went to see the{Giants Cave}and we went under an arch. There are over a{thousand new trees being planted}at about a hectare a year. Dr. Katherine Wyndham is chopping down old tress. I saw a spider eating a little bug the bug had been caught in the cobweb. I found a pheasants feather. The new trees are mostly{oak and } {ash,}and the trees she is cutting down are mostly{beech trees. } The new trees have plastic tubes round them to protect them. We all did bark rubbings. (Gloria Aged 7)
